7. DHCP Constants -> 7.3. DHCP Message T:
{
    "7.3. DHCP Message Types": [
        {
            "Original": "DHCP defines the following message types.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The formats of these messages are provided in Sections8 and 9.",
            "Adjusted": "The formats of these DHCP messages are provided in Sections 8 and 9."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Additional message types have been defined and may be defined in the future; see <<https://www.iana.org/assignments/dhcpv6-parameters>>.",
            "Adjusted": "Additional DHCP message types have been defined and may be defined in the future; see https://www.iana.org/assignments/dhcpv6-parameters."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The numeric encoding for each message type is shown in parentheses.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "SOLICIT (1) A client sends a Solicit message to locate servers.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "ADVERTISE (2) A server sends an Advertise message to indicate that it is available for DHCP service, in response to a Solicit message received from a client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "REQUEST (3) A client sends a Request message to request configuration parameters, including addresses and/or delegated prefixes, from a specific server.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "CONFIRM (4) A client sends a Confirm message to any available server to determine whether the addresses it was assigned are still appropriate to the link to which the client is connected.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "RENEW (5) A client sends a Renew message to the server that originally provided the client's leases and configuration parameters to extend the lifetimes on the leases assigned to the client and to update other configuration parameters.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "REBIND (6) A client sends a Rebind message to any available server to extend the lifetimes on the leases assigned to the client and to update other configuration parameters; this message is sent after a client receives no response to a Renew message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "REPLY (7) A server sends a Reply message containing assigned leases and configuration parameters in response to a Solicit, Request, Renew, or Rebind message received from a client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A server sends a Reply message containing configuration parameters in response to an Information-request message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A server sends a Reply message in response to a Confirm message confirming or denying that the addresses assigned to the client are appropriate to the link to which the client is connected.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A server sends a Reply message to acknowledge receipt of a Release or Decline message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "RELEASE (8) A client sends a Release message to the server that assigned leases to the client to indicate that the client will no longer use one or more of the assigned leases.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "DECLINE (9) A client sends a Decline message to a server to indicate that the client has determined that one or more addresses assigned by the server are already in use on the link to which the client is connected.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "RECONFIGURE (10) A server sends a Reconfigure message to a client to inform the client that the server has new or updated configuration parameters and that the client is to initiate a Renew/Reply, Rebind/Reply, or Information-request/Reply transaction with the server in order to receive the updated information.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "INFORMATION-REQUEST (11) A client sends an Information-request message to a server to request configuration parameters without the assignment of any leases to the client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "RELAY-FORW (12) A relay agent sends a Relay-forward message to relay messages to servers, either directly or through another relay agent.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The received message -- either a client message or a Relay-forward message from another relay agent -- is encapsulated in an option in the Relay-forward message.",
