14. Transmission of Messages by a Client:
{
    "14. Transmission of Messages by a Client -> 14.1. Rate Limiting": [
        {
            "Original": "In order to avoid prolonged message bursts that may be caused by possible logic loops, a DHCP client MUST limit the rate of DHCP messages it transmits or retransmits.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "One example is that a client obtains an address or delegated prefix but does not like the response, so it reverts back to the Solicit procedure, discovers the same (sole) server, requests an address or delegated prefix, and gets the same address or delegated prefix as before (as the server has this previously requested lease assigned to this client).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "This loop can repeat infinitely if there is not a quit/stop mechanism.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Therefore, a client must not initiate transmissions too frequently.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A recommended method for implementing the rate-limiting function is a token bucket (see [Appendix A of [RFC3290]](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc3290#appendix-A)), limiting the average rate of transmission to a certain number in a certain time interval.",
            "Adjusted": "A recommended method for implementing the rate-limiting function is a token bucket (see Appendix A of RFC3290), limiting the average rate of transmission to a certain number in a certain time interval."
        },
        {
            "Original": "This method of bounding burstiness also guarantees that the long-term transmission rate will not be exceeded.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A transmission rate limit SHOULD be configurable.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A possible default could be 20 packets in 20 seconds.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "For a device that has multiple interfaces, the limit MUST be enforced on a per-interface basis.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Rate limiting of forwarded DHCP messages and server-side messages is out of scope for this specification.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        }
    ]
}

