        },
        {
            "Original": "However, as the client SHOULD renew/rebind all IAs from the server at the same time, the client MUST select T1 and T2 times from all IA options that will guarantee that the client initiates transmissions of Renew/Rebind messages not later than at the T1/T2 times associated with any of the client's bindings (earliest T1/T2).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "At time T1, the client initiates a Renew/Reply message exchange to extend the lifetimes on any leases in the IA.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A client MUST also initiate a Renew/Reply message exchange before time T1 if the client's link-local address used in previous interactions with the server is no longer valid and it is willing to receive Reconfigure messages.",
            "Adjusted": "A client MUST also initiate a Renew/Reply message exchange before time T1 if the client's link-local address used in previous interactions with the server is no longer valid and the client is willing to receive Reconfigure messages."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If T1 or T2 had been set to 0 by the server (for an IA_NA or IA_PD) or there are no T1 or T2 times (for an IA_TA) in a previous Reply, the client may, at its discretion, send a Renew or Rebind message, respectively.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MUST follow the rules defined in Section 14.2.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client sets the \"msg-type\" field to RENEW.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client generates a transaction ID and inserts this value in the \"transaction-id\" field.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MUST include a Server Identifier option (see Section 21.3) in the Renew message, identifying the server with which the client most recently communicated.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MUST include a Client Identifier option (see Section 21.2) to identify itself to the server.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client adds any appropriate options, including one or more IA options.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MUST include an Elapsed Time option (see Section 21.9) to indicate how long the client has been trying to complete the current DHCP message exchange.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "For IAs to which leases have been assigned, the client includes a corresponding IA option containing an IA Address option for each address assigned to the IA and an IA Prefix option for each prefix assigned to the IA.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MUST NOT include addresses and prefixes in any IA option that the client did not obtain from the server or that are no longer valid (that have a valid lifetime of 0).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MAY include an IA option for each binding it desires but has been unable to obtain.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "In this case, if the client includes the IA_PD option to request prefix delegation, the client MAY include the IA Prefix option encapsulated within the IA_PD option, with the \"IPv6-prefix\" field set to 0 and the \"prefix-length\" field set to the desired length of the prefix to be delegated.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The server MAY use this value as a hint for the prefix length.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client SHOULD NOT include an IA Prefix option with the \"IPv6-prefix\" field set to 0 unless it is supplying a hint for the prefix length.",
            "Adjusted": "The client SHOULD NOT include an IA Prefix option with the \"IPv6-prefix\" field set to 0 unless the client is supplying a hint for the prefix length."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client includes an Option Request option (see Section 21.7) to request the SOL_MAX_RT option (see Section 21.24) and any other options the client is interested in receiving.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MAY include options with data values as hints to the server about parameter values the client would like to have returned.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
