{
    "18. DHCP Configuration Exchanges -> 18.2. Client Behavior -> 18.2.9. Receipt of Advertise Messages": [
        {
            "Original": "Upon receipt of one or more valid Advertise messages, the client selects one or more Advertise messages based upon the following criteria.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "\\- Those Advertise messages with the highest server preference value SHOULD be preferred over all other Advertise messages.",
            "Adjusted": "Those Advertise messages with the highest server preference value SHOULD be preferred over all other Advertise messages."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MAY choose a less preferred server if that server has a better set of advertised parameters, such as the available set of IAs, as well as the set of other configuration options advertised.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "\\- Within a group of Advertise messages with the same server preference value, a client MAY select those servers whose Advertise messages advertise information of interest to the client.",
            "Adjusted": "Within a group of Advertise messages with the same server preference value, a client MAY select those servers whose Advertise messages advertise information of interest to the client."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Once a client has selected Advertise message(s), the client will typically store information about each server, such as the server preference value, addresses advertised, when the advertisement was received, and so on.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "In practice, this means that the client will maintain independent per-IA state machines for each selected server.",
            "Adjusted": "In practice, storing information about each selected server means that the client will maintain independent per-IA state machines for each selected server."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the client needs to select an alternate server in the case that a chosen server does not respond, the client chooses the next server according to the criteria given above.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MUST process any SOL_MAX_RT option (seeSection 21.24) and INF_MAX_RT option (see Section 21.25) present in an Advertise message, even if the message contains a Status Code option (see Section 21.13) indicating a failure, and the Advertise message will be discarded by the client.",
            "Adjusted": "The client MUST process any SOL_MAX_RT option (see Section 21.24) and INF_MAX_RT option (see Section 21.25) present in an Advertise message, even if the message contains a Status Code option (see Section 21.13) indicating a failure, and the Advertise message will be discarded by the client."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A client SHOULD only update its SOL_MAX_RT and INF_MAX_RT values if all received Advertise messages that contained the corresponding option specified the same value; otherwise, it should use the default value (see Section 7.6).",
            "Adjusted": "A client SHOULD only update its SOL_MAX_RT and INF_MAX_RT values if all received Advertise messages that contained the corresponding option specified the same value; otherwise, the client should use the default value (see Section 7.6)."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MUST ignore any Advertise message that contains no addresses (IA Address options (see Section 21.6) encapsulated in IA_NA options (see Section 21.4) or IA_TA options (see Section 21.5)) and no delegated prefixes (IA Prefix options (see Section 21.22) encapsulated in IA_PD options (see Section 21.21)), with the exception that the client: \\- MUST process an included SOL_MAX_RT option and \\- MUST process an included INF_MAX_RT option.",
            "Adjusted": "The client MUST ignore any Advertise message that contains no addresses (IA Address options (see Section 21.6) encapsulated in IA_NA options (see Section 21.4) or IA_TA options (see Section 21.5)) and no delegated prefixes (IA Prefix options (see Section 21.22) encapsulated in IA_PD options (see Section 21.21)), with the exception that the client MUST process an included SOL_MAX_RT option and MUST process an included INF_MAX_RT option."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A client can record in an activity log or display to the user any associated status message(s).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client ignoring an Advertise message MUST NOT restart the Solicit retransmission timer.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "18. DHCP Configuration Exchanges -> 18.2. Client Behavior -> 18.2.10. Receipt of Reply Messages": [
        {
            "Original": "Upon the receipt of a valid Reply message in response to a Solicit with a Rapid Commit option (seeSection 21.14), Request, Confirm, Renew, Rebind, or Information-request message, the client extracts the top-level Status Code option (see Section 21.13) if present.",
            "Adjusted": "Upon the receipt of a valid Reply message in response to a Solicit with a Rapid Commit option (see Section 21.14), Request, Confirm, Renew, Rebind, or Information-request message, the client extracts the top-level Status Code option (see Section 21.13) if present."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MUST process any SOL_MAX_RT option (see Section 21.24) and INF_MAX_RT option (see Section 21.25) present in a Reply message, even if the message contains a Status Code option indicating a failure.",
