        {
            "Original": "Otherwise (no status code or another status code), the client processes the Reply as described below based on the original message for which the Reply was received.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client MAY choose to report any status code or message from the Status Code option in the Reply message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "When a client received a configuration option in an earlier Reply and then sends a Renew, Rebind, or Information-request and the requested option is not present in the Reply, the client SHOULD stop using the previously received configuration information.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "In other words, the client should behave as if it never received this configuration option and return to the relevant default state.",
