            "Original": "This document introduces two security mechanisms for the authentication of DHCP messages: (1) authentication (and encryption) of messages sent between servers and relay agents using IPsec and (2) protection against misconfiguration of a client caused by a Reconfigure message sent by a malicious DHCP server.",
