21. DHCP Options:
{
    "21. DHCP Options": [
        {
            "Original": "Options are used to carry additional information and parameters in DHCP messages.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Every option shares a common base format, as described inSection 21.1.",
            "Adjusted": "Every option shares a common base format, as described in Section 21.1."
        },
        {
            "Original": "All values in options are represented in network byte order.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "This document describes the DHCP options defined as part of the base DHCP specification.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Other options may be defined in the future in separate documents.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "See [RFC7227] for guidelines regarding the definition of new options.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "See Section 24 for additional information about the DHCPv6 \"Option Codes\" registry maintained by IANA.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Unless otherwise noted, each option may appear only in the options area of a DHCP message and may appear only once.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If an option does appear multiple times, each instance is considered separate and the data areas of the options MUST NOT be concatenated or otherwise combined.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Options that are allowed to appear only once are called \"singleton options\".",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The only non-singleton options defined in this document are the IA_NA (see Section 21.4), IA_TA (see Section 21.5), Vendor Class (see Section 21.16), Vendor-specific Information (see Section 21.17), and IA_PD (see Section 21.21) options.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Also, IA Address (see Section 21.6) and IA Prefix (see Section 21.22) may appear in their respective IA options more than once.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        }
    ]
}

18. DHCP Configuration Exchanges -> 18.3:
{
    "18. DHCP Configuration Exchanges -> 18.3. Server Behavior -> 18.3.5. Receipt of Rebind Messages": [
        {
            "Original": "SeeSection 18.4 for details regarding the handling of Rebind messages received via unicast.",
            "Adjusted": "See Section 18.4 for details regarding the handling of Rebind messages received via unicast."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Unicast transmission of Rebind messages is not allowed, regardless of whether the Server Unicast option (see Section 21.12) is configured or not.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "When the server receives a Rebind message that contains an IA option from a client, it locates the client's binding and verifies that the information in the IA from the client matches the information stored for that client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the server finds the client entry for the IA and the server determines that the addresses or delegated prefixes in the IA are appropriate for the link to which the client's interface is attached according to the server's explicit configuration information, the server SHOULD send the IA back to the client with new lifetimes and, if applicable, T1/T2 values.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the server is unable to extend the lifetimes of an address in the IA, the server MAY choose not to include the IA Address option (see Section 21.6) for this address.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the server is unable to extend the lifetimes of a delegated prefix in the IA, the server MAY choose not to include the IA Prefix option (see Section 21.22) for this prefix.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the server finds that the client entry for the IA and any of the addresses or delegated prefixes are no longer appropriate for the link to which the client's interface is attached according to the server's explicit configuration information, the server returns those addresses or delegated prefixes to the client with lifetimes of 0.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the server cannot find a client entry for the IA, the server checks if the IA contains addresses (for IA_NAs and IA_TAs) or delegated prefixes (for IA_PDs).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The server checks if the addresses and delegated prefixes are appropriate for the link to which the client's interface is attached according to the server's explicit configuration information.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "For any address that is not appropriate for the link to which the client's interface is attached, the server MAY include the IA Address option with lifetimes of 0.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "For any delegated prefix that is not appropriate for the link to which the client's interface is attached, the server MAY include the IA Prefix option with lifetimes of 0.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The Reply with lifetimes of 0 constitutes an explicit notification to the client that the specific addresses and delegated prefixes are no longer valid and MUST NOT be used by the client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the server chooses to not include any IAs containing IA Address or IA Prefix options with lifetimes of 0 and the server does not include any other IAs with leases and/or status codes, the server does not send a Reply message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "In this situation, the server discards the Rebind message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Otherwise, for each IA for which the server cannot find a client entry, the server has the following choices, depending on the server's policy and configuration information: \\- If the server is configured to create new bindings as a result of processing Rebind messages (also see the note below about the Rapid Commit option (Section 21.14)), the server SHOULD create a binding and return the IA with allocated leases with lifetimes and, if applicable, T1/T2 values and other information requested by the client.",
            "Adjusted": "Otherwise, for each IA for which the server cannot find a client entry, the server has the following choices, depending on the server's policy and configuration information: - If the server is configured to create new bindings as a result of processing Rebind messages (also see the note below about the Rapid Commit option (Section 21.14)), the server SHOULD create a binding and return the IA with allocated leases with lifetimes and, if applicable, T1/T2 values and other information requested by the client."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The server MUST NOT return any addresses or delegated prefixes in the IA that the server does not assign to the client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "\\- If the server is configured to create new bindings as a result of processing Rebind messages but the server will not assign any leases to an IA, the server returns the IA option containing a Status Code option (see Section 21.13) with the NoAddrsAvail or NoPrefixAvail status code and a status message for a user.",
            "Adjusted": "- If the server is configured to create new bindings as a result of processing Rebind messages but the server will not assign any leases to an IA, the server returns the IA option containing a Status Code option (see Section 21.13) with the NoAddrsAvail or NoPrefixAvail status code and a status message for a user."
        },
        {
            "Original": "\\- If the server does not support creation of new bindings for the client sending a Rebind message or if this behavior is disabled according to the server's policy or configuration information, the server returns the IA option containing a Status Code option with the NoBinding status code and a status message for a user.",
            "Adjusted": "- If the server does not support creation of new bindings for the client sending a Rebind message or if this behavior is disabled according to the server's policy or configuration information, the server returns the IA option containing a Status Code option with the NoBinding status code and a status message for a user."
        },
        {
            "Original": "When the server creates new bindings for the IA, it is possible that other servers also create bindings as a result of receiving the same Rebind message; see the \"DISCUSSION\" text in Section 21.14.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Therefore, the server SHOULD only create new bindings during processing of a Rebind message if the server is configured to respond with a Reply message to a Solicit message containing the Rapid Commit option.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The server constructs a Reply message by setting the \"msg-type\" field to REPLY and copying the transaction ID from the Rebind message into the \"transaction-id\" field.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The server MUST include in the Reply message a Server Identifier option (see Section 21.3) containing the server's DUID and the Client Identifier option (see Section 21.2) from the Rebind message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The server includes other options containing configuration information to be returned to the client as described in Section 18.3.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The server MAY include options containing the IAs and values for other configuration parameters, even if those IAs and parameters were not requested in the Rebind message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The T1 or T2 values set in each applicable IA option for a Reply MUST be the same values across all IAs.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The server MUST determine the T1 or T2 values across all of the applicable client's bindings in the Reply.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "This facilitates the client being able to renew all of the bindings at the same time.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        }
    ]
}

