        },
        {
            "Original": "A client MUST use the refresh time IRT_MINIMUM if it receives the option with a value less than IRT_MINIMUM.",
            "Adjusted": "A client MUST use the refresh time IRT_MINIMUM if it receives the Information Refresh Time option with a value less than IRT_MINIMUM."
        },
        {
            "Original": "As per Section 7.7, the value 0xffffffff is taken to mean \"infinity\" and implies that the client should not refresh its configuration data without some other trigger (such as detecting movement to a new link).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If a client contacts the server to obtain new data or refresh some existing data before the refresh time expires, then it SHOULD also refresh all data covered by this option.",
            "Adjusted": "If a client contacts the server to obtain new data or refresh some existing data before the refresh time expires, then it SHOULD also refresh all data covered by the Information Refresh Time option."
        },
        {
            "Original": "When the client detects that the refresh time has expired, it SHOULD try to update its configuration data by sending an Information-request as specified in Section 18.2.6, except that the client MUST delay sending the first Information-request by a random amount of time between 0 and INF_MAX_DELAY.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A client MAY have a maximum value for the refresh time, where that value is used whenever the client receives this option with a value higher than the maximum.",
            "Adjusted": "A client MAY have a maximum value for the refresh time, where that value is used whenever the client receives the Information Refresh Time option with a value higher than the maximum."
        },
        {
            "Original": "This also means that the maximum value is used when the received value is \"infinity\".",
            "Adjusted": "This also means that the maximum value is used when the received Information Refresh Time option value is \"infinity\"."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A maximum value might make the client less vulnerable to attacks based on forged DHCP messages.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Without a maximum value, a client may be made to use wrong information for a possibly infinite period of time.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
